Cheryl Anne Belmont, a daughter of Dr. and Mrs. Judson R. Belmont of Meredith, N.H., is to be married this afternoon to Neil Scott Nichols, a son of Mr. and Mrs. Leonard J. Nichols of Roslyn, N.Y. Rabbi Arthur Starr is to officiate at the Goddard Chapel at Tufts University in Medford, Mass.

The couple, both 24, graduated from Tufts, the bride magna cum laude and the bridegroom cum laude. They are now studying for medical degrees at the Tufts School of Medicine.

The bride's father, an otolaryngologist and head and neck surgeon, maintains practices in Manchester and Nashua, N.H.

Her mother, Janice Belmont, plays the French horn with the Carter Mountain Brass Quartet.

The bridegroom's mother, Arlene Nichols, who is retired, taught the second grade at the Howell Road Elementary School in Valley Stream, N.Y. His father is a lawyer and certified public accountant in Roslyn, N.Y.